# Maintainer playbook (local only)

Copy to **`MAINTAINER.md`** in the bundle root via `./snippets/bootstrap-maintainer-local.sh`. Gitignored ‚Äî do not commit org names, internal repo slugs, or machine-specific paths.

## Bootstrap

```bash
cd "$WORKFLOWS_BUNDLE_PATH"
./snippets/bootstrap-maintainer-local.sh
./snippets/verify-maintainer-local.sh
```

Re-run `./snippets/bootstrap-maintainer-local.sh --refresh-commands` after bundle bumps to refresh local slash commands.

## Local setup

| Field | Your value |
|-------|------------|
| `WORKFLOWS_BUNDLE_PATH` | e.g. `~/Repos/lsi/current/cursor-dev-workflows` |
| Adopter repos | `../video-encoder`, `../web`, `../agents/ai-agent` |
| OpenSpec | `openspec/changes/<slug>/` (tracked) |
| Layout (adopters) | **LSI only** ‚Äî `.lsi/workflows/` (see [docs/adoption-layout.md](docs/adoption-layout.md)) |
| Layout (this repo) | **Source** ‚Äî `docs/workflows/` + `overlays/lsi/` (no `.lsi/workflows/`) |

## Anti-patterns

- **Never** run `python3 snippets/adopt.py --target .` on the bundle.
- **Never** commit `MAINTAINER.md`, `AGENTS-LOCAL.md`, or `.cursor/commands/`.

## OpenSpec workflow (tracked)

Changes live under **`openspec/`** (committed with implementation):

```text
openspec/
  config.yaml
  changes/<slug>/proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md
  specs/                    # after /opsx:sync
  changes/archive/          # after close/archive
```

1. `/opsx:propose <slug>` or copy `openspec/changes/_template/` ‚Üí `openspec/changes/<slug>/`
2. Branch `feat/<slug>` or `chore/bundle-<slug>` off `main`
3. `/opsx:apply` then commit tracked files including `openspec/` deltas
4. `/lsi:close` on **`main`** after merge ‚Äî sync + archive per overlay

Trello/git-trello is optional for bundle work; branch slug may match OpenSpec slug alone.

## Adopt / re-sync loop

After every bundle release (`VERSION` + tag):

```bash
cd "$WORKFLOWS_BUNDLE_PATH"

python3 snippets/adopt.py --target ../video-encoder --config patches/video-encoder.yaml --accept-policy-defaults
python3 snippets/adopt.py --target ../web --config patches/web.yaml
python3 snippets/adopt.py --target ../agents/ai-agent --config patches/ai-agent.yaml
```

First adopt on a repo with drift: `--audit-only` first, commit `patches/files/<repo>/audit-resolutions.yaml`, then adopt with `--accept-resolutions` if needed.

## Verify all adopters

```bash
./snippets/verify-all-adopters.sh
```

Per repo: `python3 snippets/verify-adopters.py --repo-root ../web`

## Register a new adopter

[docs/adopt-new-repo.md](docs/adopt-new-repo.md) ‚Äî add `patches/<repo>.yaml`, update [patches/README.md](patches/README.md), add adopt line above.

## CI: `check_version.py`

Adopt copies `scripts/check_version.py` ‚Äî pipelines are not auto-edited. Snippets: [docs/ci/check_version-web.yml](docs/ci/check_version-web.yml), [docs/ci/check_version-ai-agent.yml](docs/ci/check_version-ai-agent.yml).

## Pre-release checklist (bundle)

- [ ] Update `## [Unreleased]` in [CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md)
- [ ] `./snippets/verify-all-adopters.sh` after adopt dry-run on each adopter
- [ ] `python3 snippets/test_adoption_verify_links.py`
- [ ] Classify bump per [docs/versioning.md](docs/versioning.md)

## Release checklist (bundle)

- [ ] `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD` in CHANGELOG; set [VERSION](VERSION)
- [ ] Tag `vX.Y.Z` on release branch
- [ ] Re-sync all adopters; open app-repo PRs with `BUNDLE_VERSION` bump in `PROJECT.md`

## Manual smoke (local kit)

1. `./snippets/bootstrap-maintainer-local.sh` on fresh clone
2. `git status` ‚Äî no staged gitignored paths
3. Cursor: `local-maintainer.mdc` + `commit-pr-conventions.mdc` active; `/opsx:propose` visible
4. `/opsx:propose test-slug` creates `openspec/changes/test-slug/`; smoke `/opsx:apply` (docs-only)
